sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Script Execution From Temp Folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a suspicious script executions from temporary folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Max Altgelt (Nextron Systems), Tim Shelton

match_context.values: @{Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; CurrentDirectory=C:\Windows\system32\; OriginalFileName=PowerShell.EXE; Hashes=SHA1=A72C41316307889E43FE8605A0DCA4A72E72A011,MD5=DCAADF7C9610B5EBEBDEDB1569EC4A9D,SHA256=D783BA6567FAF10FDFF2D0EA3864F6756862D6C733C7F4467283DA81AEDC3A80,IMPHASH=E09C4F82A1DA13A09F4FF2E625FEBA20; Description=Windows PowerShell; EventID=1; ParentCommandLine="C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Local\NotifyAgent\Node\NotifyAgent.exe"; CommandLine="powershell.exe" -WindowStyle Hidden Add-MpPreference -ExclusionPath @('C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Local\Temp\'); Add-MpPreference -ExclusionProcess 'RuntimeBroker.exe'; Add-MpPreference -ExclusionProcess 'wtmp_934761582.exe'; Add-MpPreference -ExclusionProcess 'wtmp_8003576941.exe'; FileVersion=10.0.22621.2361 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentImage=C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Local\NotifyAgent\Node\NotifyAgent.exe; IntegrityLevel=High; Image=C:\Windows\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: This signature detects the presence of a number of Windows API functionality often seen within embedded executables. When this signature alerts on an executable, it is not an indication of malicious behavior. However, if seen firing in other file types, deeper investigation may be warranted.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: InQuest Labs
